  "prompt": "How do I to deal with wealth manager?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for dealing with a wealth manager:\n\n1. Research and choose carefully\n- Check credentials and reputation\n- Understand their fee structure\n- Verify their fiduciary status\n\n2. Be clear about your financial goals\n- Short-term and long-term objectives\n- Risk tolerance\n- Investment preferences\n\n3. Ask questions\n- About investment strategies\n- Potential returns\n- Risk management\n- Performance tracking\n\n4. Understand their compensation\n- Commission-based\n- Fee-only\n- Percentage of assets managed\n\n5. Request a comprehensive financial plan\n- Asset allocation\n- Retirement planning\n- Tax strategies\n- Estate planning\n\n6. Review performance regularly\n- Annual reviews\n- Compare against benchmarks\n- Discuss portfolio adjustments\n\n7. Maintain open communication\n- Share life changes\n- Discuss concerns\n- Stay informed about investments\n\n8. Be realistic\n- No guaranteed returns\n- Understand market volatility\n- Diversification is key\n\n9. Check for potential conflicts of interest\n- Recommended products\n- Affiliated investments\n- Transparency in recommendations\n\n10. Trust your instincts\n- If something feels uncomfortable\n- Don't hesitate to seek second opinions\n- Consider changing managers if needed",
